From 3a563e1fe20187a590339deb56bf0fba4719bb68 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Colin Walters <walters@verbum.org>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 01:44:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] ipe: Add overlay_verity_validated property for composefs
 trust

Add a new IPE property 'overlay_verity_validated' that evaluates to TRUE
when a file is accessed through an overlayfs mount where the overlay's
verity validation has confirmed the file's content matches the fs-verity
digest recorded in the metadata layer.

This enables IPE policies for composefs-style integrity: a signed EROFS
metadata image records per-file fs-verity digests, overlayfs enforces
them with verity=require, and IPE gates execution based on successful
validation. An example policy rule:

  op=EXECUTE overlay_verity_validated=TRUE action=ALLOW
  DEFAULT op=EXECUTE action=DENY

Key design decisions:
- The ipe_eval_ctx carries both the data inode (d_real_inode, used for
  fsverity_digest/fsverity_signature) and the overlay inode (used for
  overlay_verity_validated), as these are different inodes
- DCACHE_OP_REAL identifies stacked filesystem dentries; non-overlay
  inodes have the flag zero-initialized so the property fails safe
- The ovl_verity_validated bool transitions monotonically false->true
  and uses WRITE_ONCE/READ_ONCE for lock-free read-side access
- Lower layers are assumed immutable (the composefs model)

Includes KUnit test cases for policy parsing of the new property.

Assisted-by: OpenCode (Claude Opus 4)
